      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "WESTERN LADY (8) was on the quick turnaround over 1800m here last time out, missing by 1.1L as a short-priced favourite. Up in trip again today is no issue and the tongue tie is applied. She draws much better this time around and she can bounce back to winning ways today. FEY KING (5) got back to winning ways last time out over 2100m at Belmont 10 days ago and as he continues to work his way back after over 2 years on the sidelines. CJP rides now from a favourable alley and with further improvement on the cards, he can get the job done again. AUDIO BOY (2) rarely turns in a poor effort, beaten 1L last start over this track and trip last time out. Nottle remains in the saddle and she draws a little better today. Keep safe. CHEYNE BAY (3) is ticking along nicely in his past couple and won't be far away. PHAROAH SHOW (4) fitter again now and can be in the finish again.",
